<DOCNO> XIE19980331.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese National Conference on Film-Making </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A national conference on
film-making, sponsored by China's Radio, Film and Television
Bureau, was held from March 28-30 in Nanchang, the capital of
Jiangxi Province,.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guan'gen, a member of the CPC Central Committee Political
Bureau, asked the film industry to work harder to welcome the 50th
anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Ding, who is head of the CPC Central Committee Publicity
Department, said that more Chinese artists have adopted correct
thinking in their film making and there have been a number of best
selling films in the country.
</P>
<P>
China has achieved certain things in restructuring its film
industry, improving management, increasing investment, and
exploring the film market, Ding said, and in broadening the
recreation industry and challenging foreign best-selling films.
</P>
<P>
He said that an important CPC principle is respecting the rule
of art and the creative work of writers and artists, and the only
way out for the country's film industry is in carrying out the
reforms. This requires ideological emancipation, seeking truth
from facts, making active probes, and being bold in practise, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that more excellent films will be
produced next year, the fiftieth anniversary of the People's
Republic of China, to push the country's film industry to what he
called its "third peak of development". 
</P>
</TEXT>
