<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province and Hong Kong Arrange Cooperation Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held today in
Guangzhou, the capital of China's Guangdong Province, to celebrate
the establishment of the Joint Conference on Guangdong-Hong Kong
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The group, which will meet twice yearly, held its first meeting
today.
</P>
<P>
Liao Hui, head of the State Council's Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office, spoke at the ceremony and conveyed Vice-Premier
Qian Qichen's congratulations on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The idea for the conference was put forth by HKSAR Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa, who also spoke today and explained that
the group was established for Hong Kong's long-term development.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong should have a far-sighted approach and a
more positive attitude towards high-level links with its neighbor
to create a better investment and policy environment.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's Governor Lu Ruihua, who also spoke, praised the
HKSAR for its remarkable success in social and economic stability
in spite of the current financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The conference is expected to help Guangdong-Hong Kong
cooperation enter a new period, Lu said, and it means that
cooperation has gone from non-government activities, before Hong
Kong's return, to more government-backed efforts under the "one
Country, two Systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
Various government officials were also present at today's
ceremony. Li Changchun, a member of the CPC Central Committee's
Political Bureau and the Secretary of the Provincial CPC
Committee, met with Tung Chee Hwa during the ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
