<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 15:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Vows to Protect Turkish Cypriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem on Monday said that Turkey is determined to defend the rights
and freedom of Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cem made the announcement at a press conference held in the
northern part of the divided Nicosia, where he is on a visit to
the Turkish-Cypriots controlled part of Cyprus, according to a
press release issued by the Turkish Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
"Any provocation or aggression directed against you
(Turkish-Cypriots) from the Aegean to the Mediterranean will be
treated as directed towards us," Cem said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Greek military build-up and planned
deployment of Russian-made S-300 missiles pose a threat not only
to Turkish Cypriots but to Turkey itself as well.
</P>
<P>
Cem said that Turkey always attaches special importance to
the security of Turkish Cypriots, adding that no body should
have doubt on Turkey's determination to protect their brothers
on the island.
</P>
<P>
"Let this be known to all, whether friends or foes, and
let them watch their steps," the foreign minister said in a
tough tone.
</P>
<P>
As to the European Union (EU)'s invitation to Cyprus for
the EU enlargement process, Cem claimed that it constitutes not
only an open violation of international law but also a denial of
reality in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
He warned that what the EU is doing will increase the
tensions between Greek and Turkish Cypriots and make the
situation in the eastern Mediterranean region more complicated.
</P>
<P>
"We once again call upon the EU to evaluate its future
steps very carefully before it is too late and before the
Greek Cypriot administration paves the way towards another war
in the island," he said.
</P>
<P>
The EU on Monday formally started its eastward enlargement
process by opening negotiations with the first wave of EU
membership candidates which also includes Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Turkey was greatly annoyed by the EU decision to invite
Cyprus to the process, saying that the Greek Cypriot-dominated
administration has no right to apply for the EU membership on
behalf of the whole island.
</P>
<P>
"We want you to stay independent. But remember that, if
pressure and oppression leave you with no other alternative, the
possibility of and the decision to integration with Turkey is
always yours," Cem said.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash also made statements on
different occasions that Turkish Cypriots will integrate with
Turkey if Cyprus is really be admitted into the European body.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into Greek-Cypriots dominated south
and the Turkish-Cypriots controlled north since 1974 when Turkish
troops intervened and took over the northern third of the
island in the wake of a pro-Athens coup in Nicosia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
