<HEADLINE> Hamas Car Bomb Causes Ramallah Explosion: TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian officials have
determined that the huge explosion Sunday night in West Bank city
Ramallah was caused by a car bomb perpetrated by Hamas, Israeli
state television reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion came after Palestinian security forces conducted
initial probe into the blast that ripped through a section of a
building in the industrial zone of Ramallah, killing two
supposedly Hamas members.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the car bomb exploded accidentally when
two Hamas bombers was heading for Israel to launch a terror
attack. The driver was killed immediately in the huge blast and
the other died of wounds late in hospital. The car they were
driving was reduced to a twisted metal wreckage.
</P>
<P>
The TV report added that the order to carry out the attack was
issued by Hamas leaders in Jordanian capital Amman. There was
limited cooperation between Israeli and Palestinian security
officials in investigating the bombing, Israeli Television Channel
I reported.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) was apparently
embarassed by the incident at a time when the United States peace
envoy Dennis Ross tried to broker a deal on Israeli further
redeployment in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Israel is rejecting a redeployment more than 9 percent in West
Bank, and insisting that a connection must be made between the
implementation of pullout sand the PNA's actions to fight
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Hamas, or Islamic Resistance Movement, has refrained from
launching terror attacks against Israel since last October when
Israel released its spiritual leader Sheikh Ahmed Yassin from
prison.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian security forces have recently raided and uncovered
seven Hamas bomb factories in Gaza Strip and confiscated a large
quantity of grenades, rockets and explosives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
