<HEADLINE> El Nino-induced Drought Affects Cereal Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The El Nino-induced
drought is expected to affect cereal production in southern
Africa for 1997/98, according to a report from the United Nations
food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) and the World Food
Programme (WFP) here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the report on the crop production and food supply situation
in southern Africa, the two United Nations agencies estimated that
the countries in southern Africa would need to import a total of
4.7 million tonnes of cereals during te 1998-99 marketing year and
that the food need could rise, especially in Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
The governments in the region had taken precautionary measures
to ensure food production, including encouragement of early
plannings of drought resistant crops, water conservation measures
and the distribution of seed packs, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
