<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 30 (Xinhua)-- The National Reconciliation
Conference of Baidoa has been postponed for another 45 days for
the second time, making the new date on May 15, The faction
Ieaders representing the National Coordination Committee
(NCC) announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a press briefing shortly after the NCC meeting on Monday
evening, Ali Mahdi Mohamed who chaired the meeting said the
Baidoa conference is postponed mainly for the Iack of economy for
its convening.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mahdi also said the committee has been under going heavy
tasks in formulating an all inclusive administration for the
capital Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Somalis to work hard towards the convening of
the Baidoa conference using all the available means. "We'd also
appreciate any foreign help towards this endeavor," he added.
</P>
<P>
Hussein Mohamed Aidid who also spoke during the press briefing
vowed that the Baidoa meeting will no Ionger be postponed again.
</P>
<P>
In a document signed by the two co-chairman of the NCC, Ali
Mahdi Mohamed and Hussein Mohamed Aidid, the faction leaders
announced their agreement over the general structure of the
Mogadishu's adminstration.
</P>
<P>
The document made available for the press showed that
Mogadishu will have a one chairman (governor), six deputy
chairpersons, a secretary general, an independent judicial
council and an independent financial controller.
</P>
<P>
The document also said the air and seaports will each have a
general manager that will directly operate temporarily under the
governor's control.
</P>
<P>
Mogadishu will also have a police command control with a
police stations devision and a quick reactions devision.
</P>
<P>
Hussein Mohamed Aidid said the nominations of the individuals
for these posts will be announced within three days.
</P>
<P>
According to the signed document, members of a supreme council
of Mogadishu will be nominated, but no specific time is
mentioned.  
</P>
