<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Red Cross Society Helps Southwestern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Red Cross Society of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region and Yunnan Province signed an
agreement here today for helping Yunnan set up a disaster-relief
network.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong side will provide 5.29 million yuan for the work, all
of it coming from local donations, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Disaster-relief centers will be set up in 13 administrative
areas in Yunnan, which will function as storage, training,
information, and medical centers designed to ensure timely and
efficient rescue work in the case of various types of disasters.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan's Vice-Governor Liang Gongqin, who spoke at the signing
ceremony, placed emphasis on the need for these relief centers
because the many calamities in the province last year caused more
than 10 billion yuan in losses.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been a major source of donations for Yunnan when
it has suffered from calamities. 
</P>
