<HEADLINE> China Getting Rid of More Textile Spindles in Northern Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China's Hebei Province
joined the nationwide spindle smashing campaign today by
destroying 41,000 outdated cotton spindles at local textile mills.
</P>
<P>
So far, 781,000 spindles have been destroyed in various parts
of China. The central government strategy is intended to shrink
the size of the inefficient, giant textile industry and is part of
the first efforts to restructure the state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Hebei is one of the coastal provinces and municipalities that
have led the smashing drive and plans to get rid of 710,000 cotton
spindles and lay off 48,000 workers from its textile mills in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The province is the fifth largest textile base in China. In the
1950s and '60s, it had more than 20 large state-owned textile
factories.  
</P>
</TEXT>
