<HEADLINE> Chinese Drama to Be Staged in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese drama, which is
referred to as the Chinese "Romeo and Juliet", will appear on
stage in New York in July.
</P>
<P>
The work, "Peony Pavilion", was written almost 600 years ago by
Tang Xianzu (1550-1616), and depicts a young woman who struggled
for her freedom and love and defies society, leading to her death.
</P>
<P>
The 21-hour drama will be performed over three days at the
Lincoln Center by the Shanghai Kunqu Opera Troupe. It will also be
performed in Paris, Sydney, and Hong Kong later this year.
</P>
<P>
The drama is in the Kunqu opera style, which is similar in
costume and staging to Peking opera but has music that is more
subtle and delicate. Most later dramatic forms, including Peking
Opera, were influenced to a varying degree by the Kunqu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
