<HEADLINE> Southern China Holding Regular Meetings On Anti-Corruption Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Leaders in China's southernmost
province, Hainan Island, announced today that this year, regular
briefings on their anti-corruption campaign will be held every
three months.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Haiguo, Deputy-secretary of the Disciplinary
Committee of the Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), said that the local media will be given
the latest progress reports, especially on major cases.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference today, Zhang said that in 1997, the
province recovered 3.5 million yuan in public funds from deals
involving private telephones and mobile phones that were paid for
with public money.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 1,440 official meetings were canceled or changed,
and 156 ceremonies and other types of boring official activities
were halted, resulting in savings of 29.55 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, provincial disciplinary and inspection departments
handled 818 graft cases and 785 officials received penalties in
accordance with CPC or government codes of conduct. 
</P>
