<HEADLINE> URGENT, Chinese Premier Arrives in London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji arrived
here Tuesday afternoon for a three-day official visit to Britain
at the invitation of British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the first by a Chinese premier in 13 years,
Zhu will meet Queen Elizabeth II, hold talks with Blair on
bilateral and international issues of mutual concern, and meet
with British business leaders.
</P>
<P>
Zhu will also attend the Sino-EU summit and the second
Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM II) to be opened here on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
