<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN High Commissioner for Human Rights Postpones China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The UN High Commissioner for
Human Rights Mary Robinson has postponed a China visit,
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen told journalists this evening, after
talks with UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
"We hope Mrs. Robinson can visit China at an early date, but
the originally proposed date was early and not quite to her
convenience", Qian explained.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will sign the International Covenant on
Civil and Political Rights as it has announced and abide by its
rules, but that China is now studying it to see whether there are
some contradictions between it and China's laws.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that he was encouraged to hear that China has
invited Mrs. Robinson for a visit although the date has not been
fixed and that he and Mrs. Robinson are expecting to continue
cooperating with China in the field of human rights.
</P>
<P>
Annan arrived here this morning on a two-day official visit to
China as guest of the Chinese government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
