<HEADLINE> Sino-Vietnamese Border Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 Sino-Vietnamese Border
Trade Fair is scheduled for May 23-27 in Fangchenggang, a coastal
city in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Fangchenggang's population is 750,000, with ethnic minority
groups accounting for 238,000, many of them from the Jing minority.
</P>
<P>
The city's GDP rose 17.7 percent last year from the previous
year's and the port handled 9.74 million tons of cargo, up 27.9
percent from 1996, and accounting for 70 percent of the region's
port business.
</P>
<P>
The city did 2 billion yuan worth of border trade and had 35
million US dollars worth of overseas investment, a 17.6 percent
rise from 1996. 
</P>
