<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier's Presence At Europe Meeting Important: Qian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, in a
meeting today with former British Defense Secretary Michael
Portillo, said it is of great importance that Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji attend the second Asia-Europe Meeting.
</P>
<P>
It will give him an opportunity to exchange views on
multilateral issues with the heads of Asian and European nations,
Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu was elected premier at the first session of the Ninth
Chinese People's Congress this month. He left early today for
London, where the meeting will be held April 3-4. This is his
first trip abroad in the new post. He will take part in the second
Asia-Europe meeting and make an official visit to Britain and
France.
</P>
<P>
Zhu's visit to Britain and Prime Minister Tony Blair's visit to
China this year will help open a new chapter in Sino-British
relations, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
China has always underlined its friendship with Britain and
bilateral ties have gone smoothly in recent years, said Qian, who
is a long-time diplomat who recently quit his job as foreign
minister.
</P>
<P>
Portillo noted that problems between Britain and China have
begun to disappear after Hong Kong's smooth transfer of power, and
he expressed the hope that Hong Kong will serve as a bridge
instead of an obstacle between the two countries. 
</P>
