<HEADLINE> China, Canada Sign Trade and Investment Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Canadian companies
today signed 13 contracts valued at 300 million Canadian dollars
and investment agreements worth 48 million Canadian dollars in
aviation, construction work, electric power, manufacturing,
medical supplies, and education.
</P>
<P>
SLM Software, W.J.Stelmaschuk and Assoc. Ltd, the law firms
Remedios and Company and Blake, Cassels &AMP; Graydon have announced
that they will set up offices in Beijing, joining nearly 300 other
Canadian companies that are in China.
</P>
<P>
Canada's International Trade Minister Sergio Marchi, who
attended the signing ceremony, said that deals between many small
and medium-sized Canadian and Chinese businesses were made today,
indicating that the governments of both countries encourage
businesses to cooperate.
</P>
<P>
The contracts include an automated hydro-electric system for
Henan Province from CAE Electronics, 200 Yun-12 aircraft frames
from the Harbin Aircraft Manufacturing Corp. for Canadian
Aerospace Group, and the third phase of the Beijing Airport
International Warehouse being done by Davey International Inc.
</P>
