<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Intends to Retain Primakov, Zadornov as Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
indicated Tuesday that he would reappoint two senior ministers to
the new government.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said after talks with Namibian President Sam Nujoma
that he would reappoint Yevgeny Primakov and Mikhail Zadornov as
foreign and finance ministers respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, the Kremlin said that Yetsin's intention is not a
decree, as under the constitution Yeltsin cannot appoint ministers
while his choice for government prime minister has not been
confirmed by the State Duma, lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
But Kremlin spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky added that the
president's intention was clear. 
</P>
</TEXT>
