<HEADLINE> Time-Tested Pak-China Relations to Grow Stronger: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Governor of Pakistan's Punjab
Province Shahid Hamid said Tuesday the time-tested Pak-China
relations, as strong and mighty as the Karakorum Highway, will
grow stronger with the passage of time.
</P>
<P>
Hamid made the comment in Lahore, the second largest city of
Pakistan, during his meeting with a six-member Chinese goodwill
delegation, headed by Chen Hui, Vice President of Beijing People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (BPAFFC).
</P>
<P>
He said that exchange of such visits served to further deepen
the ties between the peoples and the governments of the two
friendly countries.
</P>
<P>
The exemplary friendship between the governments and the
peoples of the two countries will widen the horizons of friendship
and will remain deep-rooted in the next millennium, said the
Governor.
</P>
<P>
President of Pak-China Friendship Association Senator Faseih
Iqbal was also present on the occasion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
