<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index dropped 11.54 points Tuesday to close at 1553.06
points against Monday's close 1564.60 points.
</P>
<P>
A total trade volume of 61 million shares trade Tuesday against
44 million shares traded the previous day. There were 55 gainers,
74 losers, while share prices of 46 companies remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Analysts believed that the drop of the KSE-100 Index was a
response to the two bomb blasts that ripped parts of Karachi
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The blasts took place in a busy market and thoroughfare Tuesday
morning, killing two and leaving 24 injured.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that the stock market is expected to pick up in
the coming days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
