<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets with UN Secretary-General (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, in a
meeting with the UN's Secretary-General Kofi Annan here this
afternoon, said that China will continue to support his work in
the years to come and take an active part in UN work and make a
contribution to safeguarding world peace and promoting development.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that there have been many positive changes in the UN
since Annan took office, and the UN's active participation in
international affairs is conducive to the development of
multi-polarization in the world.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated Annan on his successful mediation during his
Iraqi visit and said he appreciates Annan's courage and wisdom in
handling the Iraqi weapons inspection crisis, saying that it was a
difficult mission which ended with very good results and
satisfaction in the international community because of Annan's
persistent efforts.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the UN's role in safeguarding world peace and
security and in easing regional tensions is important, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese hope that Iraq can cooperate with the
inspection group and implement the Security Council resolutions in
a down-to-earth manner, and that the inspection group should
continue to carry out rational inspections in a constructive way.
</P>
<P>
Annan praised China's positive role in the UN and thanked it
for its strong support and help during the recent Iraqi weapons
inspection crisis. He said that the agreement reached with the
Iraqi government is being implemented and the inspection work is
going smoothly and that he hopes the Security Council members and
the international community will continue to offer support on this
issue.
</P>
</TEXT>
