<HEADLINE> South African Trade Minister Comments on China Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) --South African Minister of Trade
and Industry Alec Erwin said in a press conference here today that
he satisfied with his Beijing visit.
</P>
<P>
The government officials and businessmen of South Africa and China
have discussed extensively on enhancing bilateral economic and
trade cooperation during the visit, Erwin said, adding that more than
five hundred businessmen participated in the South
Africa Investment and Products seminar held by South Africa here
these days and scored satisfactory results.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between China and South Africa was worth nearly
1.6 billion US dollars last
year, he said, and that it is likely to increase with joint
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Erwin noted that, as developing countries, South Africa and
China face many similar problems in improving their economies,
which complement each other a great deal. He said his country is
willing to play a positive role in bilateral economic and trade
cooperation and increase bilateral cooperation in minerals and
construction.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's development has impressed him deeply and
that its reform of the economic system will have great influence
on other countries.
</P>
<P>
Erwin will leave for Shanghai this evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
