<HEADLINE> Chinese Film Festival Scheduled for November in Southwestern City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The 7th China Golden Rooster
and Hundred Flowers Film Festival is scheduled for the city of
Chongqing from November 18 to 23.
</P>
<P>
The 21st Hundred Flowers and the 18th Golden Rooster movie
awards will be given during the one-week festival, according to
one culture official, and the China Federation of Literary and Art
Groups, the China Film Association, and the Chongqing government
will hold a series of cultural and art activities, movies, film
fairs, symposia, performances, and exchange programs.
</P>
<P>
The first festival was held in 1992, when the Hundred Flowers
Awards and the Golden Rooster Awards were combined, and it is now
the most influential film industry event in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
