<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Increase Trade With China: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Canada will enhance its economic
and trade cooperation with China and other Asian partners,
according to its International Trade Minister Sergio Marchi, who
spoke at a Canada-China Business Council luncheon here today.
</P>
<P>
Marchi said that this year is the Council's 20th anniversary,
and that it ties the two countries together and helps them
understand the many opportunities in Canada-China trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
He said that this ministerial delegation is the largest ever, a
clear demonstration that Canada values economic and trade ties
with China.
</P>
<P>
Many Canadian ministers are planning China tours in the coming
weeks, he said.
</P>
<P>
The key to expanding trade between the two countries is greater
participation by mid-sized and small enterprises, he said, and a
third of this delegation is made up of representatives of these
companies.
</P>
<P>
The Council, established in 1978, has offices in Toronto,
Vancouver, Beijing, and Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
