<HEADLINE> Maradona Goal Voted Best Ever </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona's second goal
against England in the 1986 World Cup quarter-final has been voted
the greatest goal of all time.
</P>
<P>
Footballers past and present selected their three favorite
goals and Maradona's strike was the runaway winner, getting twice
as many votes as runner-up, Marco Van Basten.
</P>
<P>
Basten's blast, for the Netherlands against the Soviet Union in
the 1988 European Championships, was voted just ahead of David
Beckham's halfway line lob against Wimbledon in the 1996/1997
English season opener. 
</P>
