<HEADLINE> HK Repatriates Vietnamese Illegal Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A group of 238 Vietnamese,
including 237 illegal immigrants and one migrant, left here by air
for Hanoi, Vietnam, Tuesday on two flights under the Orderly
Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
Most of the returnees arrived in Hong Kong in 1997, with one in
1991 and three in 1996, according to a report from the Information
Services of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The group brought to 12,098 the total number repatriated on ORP
flights since October 1991, when the Vietnamese migrant population
reached a historical peak, with over 64,300 Vietnamese people
accommodated in 14 camps in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
With the continued efforts of all parties concerned, the
present Vietnamese population in Hong Kong has dropped to about
1,200 refugees, 659 migrants and 743 illegal immigrants. 
</P>
