<HEADLINE> HK's Exchange Fund Reports Results in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) Tuesday announced the audited results of the
Exchange Fund at end-1997 with total assets up 19 percent to 636.6
billion HK dollars (81.61 billion U.S. dollars) and a 10 percent
growth in accumulated surplus.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the HKMA said that growth in the accumulated
surplus is a reflection of the performance of HKMA's steady
management of the Exchange Fund.
</P>
<P>
The 10 percent increase in a year of volatility and the most
serious financial crisis in Asia can be considered satisfactory
under difficult conditions, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the HKMA has continued to undertake a
prudent approach and pursued largely a defensive bond and currency
strategy in the first half of last year as markets were volatile.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of last year, the HKMA extended the duration
of the bond holdings as markets improved.
</P>
<P>
"The HKMA will continue with its prudent management of the
Exchange Fund in 1998 to achieve consistent returns and high
liquidity with minimum volatility, in full compliance with the
guidelines set down by Exchange Fund Advisory Committee," the
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
