-- Four years after the genocide in Rwanda, Le Figaro is
pursuing its investigation on the action by France in Rwanda. Le
Figaro learned about the origin of the two missiles which shot
down on April 6, 1994, the French military helicopter carrying
Rwandan President Juvenal Habyarimana and Burundian President
Cyprien Ntaryamira. They were from the stock of missiles seized
by French troops from Iraq during the Gulf War. The
missile-launcher could have been bought by an associate of
captain Barril, former security officer of the Elysee
presidential palace who played a dubious role in Rwanda before
the genocide. 
