<HEADLINE> Romanian Interior Minister Named Acting Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu appointed Interior Minister Gavril Dejeu as acting
prime minister Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu's decision was made after Prime Minister Victor
Ciorbea resigned from his post.
</P>
<P>
Before there is a new cabinet in two weeks, his team will only
handle routine administrative affairs and stay away from
legislative procedures, Dejeu said after the appointment.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea announced his resignation earlier in the day in an
televised address to the nation.
</P>
<P>
The pressure for Ciorbea's step-down had been constant from
parties within the ruling coalition, which accused him of
incompetence and laxity in carrying out promised economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
By constitution, his resignation meant the dissolution of the
cabinet. Therefore, President Constantinescu has reportedly begun
consultation with leaders of parliamentary parties on a new
cabinet. 
</P>
