<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State-Owned Firms Privatized in Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Two state-owned enterprises
were privatized in Eritrea iN lhne with the government's
privatization program, the latest issue of the English wedkly
Eritrea Profile reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the government's newspaper, Asmara-based Mereb
Textiles Factory was bought by Baroko Company Eritrea at 12
million Nakfa (about 1.67 million U.S. Dollars) and the bus
assembly plant, Eri-Bus, was sold to Teklehaimanot Tekleab at 2.4
million Nakfa or 330,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, eight out of the 39 formerly state-owned firms slated
for privatization have been sold out.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Eritrean government's privatization agency
announced that seven other state-owned enterprises are expected
for sale shortly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
