<DOCNO> XIE19980331.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mining Deal Sealed Between Addis and Co. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government and
the National Mining Corporation has signed a mining agreement
to give the latter an exclusive exploitation right.
</P>
<P>
The agreement signed by Minister of Mines and Energy Izaddin
Ali and General Manager Melaku Beza Monday, gives the corporation
an exclusive right to tap and mine gold within the Legadembi gold
mining area of 88.59 square kilometers in Oromiya region.
</P>
<P>
The accord stipulates that the corporation will mine gold for
the coming 20 years and explore for gold and associated minerals
for three years within the licensed area.
</P>
<P>
The corporation will spend a minimum of 18 million Birr (about
2.6 million U.S. Dollars) for exploration during the first three
years of the exploration period. And the total investment of the
corporation will be around 200 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the corporation will produce 1,200
kilograms of gold in the first year and the output is expected to
reach 11,800 kilograms in the following year.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government earns royalty on gross products, land
rent, license fees and income tax in line with the mining law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980331.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> January Light-Industry Exports Hit New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China exported 3.892 billion
U.S. dollars in light-industry products in January, up 10.31
percent from the same period last year, according to customs
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 21.2 percent are products processed from imported
materials with a value of 825 million U.S. dollars, a decrease of
2.84 percent over last January.
</P>
<P>
Exports of machinery and electronics products for light
industry use reached 1.054 billion U.S. dollars, a year-on-year
increase of 12.5 percent. In this category, all exports made
substantial gains in January except machinery for daily use,
lighting equipment, and machinery for light industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the 14 major export-oriented
light-industry products earned 2.576 billion U.S. dollars in the
first month of this year, 8.47 percent more than 1997. Hardware,
electrical appliances and plastic products grew rapidly.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by the State Statistics
Bureau, the industrial production value of light industry in
January reached 172 billion yuan based on 1990 prices, an increase
of 3.4 percent over last January.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that, the production of five out of 25 major
light-industry products increased. The five were vacuum cleaners,
dairy products, machine-made paperboard, beer and machine-made
paper.
</P>
<P>
The production of such goods as sewing machines, bicycles,
newsprint, plastic film for agricultural use and electric fans did
not change in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
