<HEADLINE> Two Killed, 24 Injured in Bomb Blasts in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Two persons were killed and 24
others injured in two bomb blasts occurred Tuesday morning in
Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi.
</P>
<P>
The first explosion took place at around 9:15 a.m. (local time)
in an ice-cream parlor, killing one person and injuring 12 others,
according to sources in Karachi.
</P>
<P>
It also damaged seven shops around the spot.
</P>
<P>
The second blast occurred at 10:05 a.m. (local time). It killed
one person and injured 12 others.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that rescue operation is under way and the
injured have been sent to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The police have been placed on "Red Alert" to keep strict vigil
against suspected vehicles and persons besides carrying out
intense checking, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
