<HEADLINE> UNICEF Executive Director to Visit Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Director of the
United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) Carol Bellamy will pay
three-day visit to Afghanistan starting from April 1.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Afghanistan, Bellamy will visit project
sites and listen to Afghans to have a better understanding of the
situation in the country so that the UNICEF can better support
Afghan children and women, said a press release issued here
Tuesday by the UNICEF.
</P>
<P>
Given the changing conditions under which humanitarian
organizations are working in Afghanistan, the release said that
all United Nations humanitarian agencies met recently in Geneva,
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
A common approach to the situation in Afghanistan has been
agreed upon and the UNICEF Executive Director will be carrying
that message to both the United Nations agencies working in the
country and to the Afghan side, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the release said that the UNICEF is particularly
concerned about the quality of and access to both health and
education services in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Previous discussions have been taken place between the United
Nations and the Afghan Taliban militia, who control the capital of
Kabul, in this regard. Some progress has been made in the area of
health, said the release.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF executive director will have discussions with the
Taliban in order to continue the dialogue on these issues, the
release said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
