<HEADLINE> Albania Praises Greece Over Refugee Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Meidani
has praised the Greek government over its policy towards the
Albanian refugees.
</P>
<P>
Meidani told a visiting Greek parliamentary delegation headed
by former Foreign Minister Karolos Papulias that relations between
the two countries were strong.
</P>
<P>
The President said Albania was thankful to the Greek government
for granting Albanian refugees legal residential rights. He hoped
the refugees would be allowed to use Albanian in their study and
cultural actitivities.
</P>
<P>
Papulias said Greece had greatly assisted Albania when it was
in difficulty, he said.
</P>
<P>
Legislation passed by the Greek parliament would create better
opportunities for Albanian refugees in their lives and education,
Papulias said.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Fatos Nano and parliament speaker Skender
Gjinushi also met with the Greek delegation.
</P>
<P>
Discussing the Kosovo crisis, both countries believed political
and diplomatic efforts were the only way to achieve a permanent
peace in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
However, the Albania prime minister also suggested that Kosovo
be granted the same status enjoyed by the Republics of Montenegro
and Serbia, without breaking away from the federal government.
</P>
</TEXT>
