<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Province Issues Warning on Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province plans to mobilize the whole society to help prevent
forest fires, according to a recent meeting here.
</P>
<P>
The province has enacted a regulation that prohibits anyone
from entering the forestry region with kindling materials through
May 31. Activities such as outdoor smoking, picnics, hunting and
firecrackers are all banned.
</P>
<P>
Strict management will be enforced in such areas as explosions
and exploration, and all forest operations prone to cause fire
should be stopped.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also banned outdoor paper and incense
burning, which are traditional acts performed by Chinese to pay
tribute to dead family members as grave-sweeping day approaches.
</P>
<P>
Forest fires are a great threat to the province, especially
with the dry conditions in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
