<HEADLINE> Retail Sales Climb in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China's retail sales amounted to
254.95 billion yuan in January, up 12.9 percent over the
corresponding period in 1997, according to the latest data from
State Statistical Bureau (SSB).
</P>
<P>
In terms of sales value, consumers in the provinces of
Guangdong, Jiangsu and Shandong ranked as the top three in
January; the retail sales were 28.61 billion yuan, 20.05 billion
yuan and 18.22 billion yuan, respectively. The three provinces
reported a year-on-year increase of 14.7 percent, 10.5 percent and
8.9 percent, respectively, in retail sales.
</P>
<P>
According to the SSB report, the country's consumer price index
reached 100.3 in January, taking that of the same month in 1997 as
100. The index for urban and rural areas stood at 100.8 and 99.8,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The highest inflation rate was registered in Beijing, of which
the consumer price index hit 104. Meanwhile, South China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region reported the biggest price drop,
with its consumer price index at 96.5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
