<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Becomes Greener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A tree-planting project launched
in 1995 has turned Tianjin, a north China port city, into a land
of greenery.
</P>
<P>
During the last three years, the city planted 42,400 hectares
of trees and completed 5.37 million square meters of landscaping,
with the greenery coverage rate reaching 21 percent. Per capita
grass land increased by 0.9 square meters, reaching 3.6 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The city has established a greenbelt surrounding the urban area
and more than 90 scenic spots in nearby suburbs.
</P>
<P>
An agricultural greenbelt has been planted in five major
suburban counties including Jixian, Wuqing, Baodi, Jinghai and
Ninghe. To date, five counties in Tianjin have 106,700 hectares of
shelter forest and commercial forest.
</P>
<P>
Jixian County has turned all 40,000 hectares of its barren
hills green; four of the five counties have achieved greenery
targets set by the state; 80 townships have completed
criss-crossing tree planting and and 1,100 villages are up to the
greenery standard.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
