<HEADLINE> Strawberry Hometown Supplies Market During All Seasons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Mouth-watering Longkou
strawberries can now be bought year-round in fruit markets as far
north as China's Heilongjiang Province and as far south as
Guangdong Province,
</P>
<P>
Longkou, a small village in east China's Shandong Province,
was named "Strawberry Hometown" by the Ministry of Agriculture
last year, when it harvested 36 million kilograms of strawberries.
</P>
<P>
The village has a decade-long strawberry-growing history, but
only in recent years it introduced new strains and planting
technology from Japan to engage in large-scale production.
</P>
<P>
Now, 90 percent of the village people are specialized
strawberry growers whose greenhouses cover 800 hectares of
land. They earned 100 million yuan last year from growing
strawberries.
</P>
<P>
The Longkou strawberry has gained in popularity because of its
sweet taste and plump flesh, longer preservation period and
brilliant red color. Each Longkou strawberry weights more than 100
grams.
</P>
<P>
Apart from occupying domestic markets, the Longkou strawberry
is also sold overseas to such countries as Japan and the Republic
of Korea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
