<HEADLINE> Black Gibbons Surviving in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen black gibbons are living
in Hainan Province, an island off the southern tip of China,
according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
The Bawangling state-level natural protection zone has 17 black
gibbons living in four groups, an increase from seven or eight in
1984.
</P>
<P>
The number of the animals under state first-category protection
increases by three each year, experts said. 
</P>
