<HEADLINE> Philippoussis Threats not to Play Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Mark Philippoussis has
threatened not to play for Australia in the Davis Cup until team
captain John Newcombe makes a public apology to him, local reports
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis accused Newcombe and Australia Davis Cup coach
Tony Roche of refusing to help him when he encountered sadness on
learning his father had cancer last year.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis, 21, was unavailable for Australia's World Group
first-round home tie against Zimbabwe to be started on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In his stand, Newcombe said he had nothing to apologise for,
saying that "you can only apologise if you've got something to
apologise for."
</P>
<P>
When Philippoussis was absent from the tie against Zimbabwe,
Australia could miss its number one singles player Pat Rafter, who
is struggling to overcome a virus.
</P>
<P>
Australia reached the Davis Cup semifinals last September
before being beaten by United States, runners-up to eventual
winners Sweden. 
</P>
