<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Signs Bill to Lease Kazakh Military Testing Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
has agreed to lease four military testing sites based in
Kazakhstan, the Itar-TASS news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The sights include the 929 National Flight Testing Center, the
4th National Testing Site, Imba Testing Site and Sarei-Shagan
Testing Site.
</P>
<P>
Russia will pay an annual rent of 27.5 million U.S. dollars for
leasing these sites. It will pay an additional separate annual
rent of 115 million U.S. for leasing the Baikonur Cosmodrome, one
of the largest launching and testing sites of the former Soviet
Union based in southwestern Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Sarei-Shagan Testing Site is designed to test missile defense
systems. Russia does not possess similar testing sites.
</P>
<P>
Imba Testing Site is designed to test air-defense missile
systems.
</P>
<P>
The agreements on leasing the testing sites were signed by the
Russian and Kazakh governments on January 20, 1995. Because they
were not approved, Russia did not pay the rent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
