<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary Experiencing Crisis in Public Order This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hungary is experiencing a
worsening condition in the disruptions of public order and other
criminal cases, official statistics revealed.
</P>
<P>
The country registered 41,700 criminal cases during the first
month of this year, an increase of 32 percent compared with the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian Central Statistics bureau announced Monday that in
one year ending in January, economic criminal cases in the country
increased nine times, while property violation cases increased by
25 percent. There was also a sharp increase in violent criminal
cases.
</P>
<P>
The criminal rate in Budapest, the Hungarian capital, has also
shown a sharp increase in crime. Crimes performed by gangs reached
4,500 cases. They account for 99.6 percent of the total of such
cases in the country, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The west states of Fejer, Gyor-Moson-Sopron and Vas, and the
north state of Heves are areas in which criminal cases occur with
greater frequency.
</P>
<P>
The worsening situation in public order is a serious social
problem for Hungary and causing much concern among residents,
officials claimed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
