<HEADLINE> Money Counterfeiting Shop Uncovered in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Polish police uncovered an
underground shop recently which had been engaged in forging coins
of zloty, the polish currency, for years, the Polish Press Agency
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The illegal shop turned out millions of coins with the face
value of five zlotys (1.5 U.S. dollars), the agency said.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources, 1 in every 50 of the five-zloty
coins in circulation in Poland is a bogus one forged by the
factory. It is believed to be one of the biggest counterfeiting
shops ever found in the country.
</P>
<P>
Some Ukrainians are also involved in the counterfeiting, police
said. They are suspected of having provided special machinery and
equipment to the shop based in Wolka Podlacka in the southeastern
province of Rzeszow.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 10 million five-zloty coins may have been
sent to Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
