<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Average Consumption Price Drops Slightly in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The consumer goods price in Vietnam
fell by 0.8 percent in March compared to the previous month, but
it was up 4.5 percent against the same period last year, official
statistics revealed Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Almost all consumer goods prices were experiencing drops this
month from 0.2 percent to 3 percent. Sharp reductions were
reported in the prices of vehicles, postal costs, housing and
construction materials, and home appliances.
</P>
<P>
Food price fell by 0.8 percent throughout the country, but
fluctuations were reported in some localities. Prices for
foodstuffs were also reduced by 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In March, the exchange rate of the U.S. dollar against the
Vietnamese dong had risen by 13.9 percent and the gold price had
dropped by 3.8 percent compared with the same month last year.
</P>
