<HEADLINE> Mexican Foreign Minister Visits Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Foreign Minister Rosario
Green made a one-day official visit to Brazil to promote bilateral
relations on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It was the first visit by the Mexican minister to Brazil, said
the Brazilian chancery.
</P>
<P>
Green met with her Brazilian counterpart Luiz Felipe Lampreia
and President of Brazil Fernando Henrique Cardoso.
</P>
<P>
Their talks covered the handling of regional and international
problems, and the Mexican initiative to create a Mexico-Brazil
commission for the next century. 
</P>
