<HEADLINE> Vietnam Urges Austria to Boost Bilateral Economic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Vietnamese Prime Minister
Phan Van Khai urged Austria to help boost economic relations
between their two countries, as well as the European Union (EU)
and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
After holding talks with Austrian Federal Chancellor Viktor
Klima on Monday, he told a news conference that improvement of
democracy could only be achieved as a result of economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Phan arrived in Vienna Monday to start a three-day official
visit to the country, the first leg of his European tour. He is
the highest-level Vietnamese leader to visit Austria so far.
</P>
<P>
Klima told the news conference that his country would make
efforts to boost economic relations between the European Union
(EU) and ASEAN. Austria will hold the rotating EU presidency
during the second half of the year.
</P>
<P>
He expressed belief that the EU could lay the foundation for
strenthening EU-ASEAN economic relations during the Second
Asia-Europe Meeting, scheduled for April 3-4.
</P>
<P>
The chancellor also pointed out that Viet Nam is a potential
partner of Austria in the fields of trade and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Phan will also visit London later to attend the forthcoming
Asia-Europe Meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
