<HEADLINE> World Bank-Funded Wastewater Treatment Project Launched in Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A wastewater treatment project
involving a World Bank loan has been launched in Wuhan, capital of
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The project, costing 1.4 billion yuan (168.67 million U.S.
dollars) including 5.63 million U.S. dollars from the World Bank,
is part of the effort to turn Wuhan into a modern garden city,
city officials said.
</P>
<P>
The investment will be used to build five wastewater treatment
plants, seven pumping stations, and 100 kilometers of pipeline.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed by 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
