<HEADLINE> Nokia Signs Contracts with Chinese Mobile-Phone Sales Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China's leading
telecommunications sales business became a wholesale and retail
franchise of Finland's Nokia, the Beijing Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
China Posts and Telecommunications Equipment Corp. (CPTEC)
signed sales contracts Monday with Beijing Nokia Mobile Telecom
Co. Ltd. for selling mobile phones and other telecommunications
products in Chinese markets.
</P>
<P>
Nokia, a worldwide giant telecommunications manufacturer, has
established numerous joint ventures for 13 years with Chinese
businesses.
</P>
<P>
CPTEC, the largest national sales entity, has a large share of
the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the contracts, CPTEC will also arrange sales
promotion for Nokia and help it fulfill after-sale services, the
report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
