<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Eliminates Lead Pollution in Downtown Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the biggest port in
northern China, has eliminated lead pollution in the downtown area
since it prohibited the use of auto fuel containing lead beginning
this year.
</P>
<P>
The ban has led to a decrease of four tons of lead pollutants
discharged into the atmosphere, according to the city's
environmental protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 automobiles cruise city streets each
day. Prior to the ban, 85 percent of the lead in the autos' fuel
had been discharged into the atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The city will also spread the application of the ban to its
suburban areas, take steps to spread the consumption of
sulfur-fixed coal, and speed up the tree-planting efforts in urban
areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
