</P>
<P>
Ciorbea would announce his resignation in a television address
to the nation. President Emil Constantinescu was expected to
accept the resignation in a separate television appearance.
(Romania-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia would firmly support the efforts made by the
United Nations to safeguard world peace and security, Russian
President Boris Yeltsin told visiting U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Monday.
</P>
<P>
When meeting Annan, who arrived here Sunday on a two-day visit,
Yeltsin stressed the United Nations' important role in helping
establish a multipolar world order.
</P>
<P>
The role of the United Nations in the modern world must be
highlighted and measures should be taken to adjust its work and
agencies to meet up-to-date challenges, the Russian president
said. (Russia-Yeltsin-Annan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan hoped that
the return to homeland of Cambodian Prince Norodom Ranariddh will
assist in the holding of free and fair elections in the country.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General welcomes the return of Prince Norodom
Ranariddh on March 30 after an absence of nearly nine months,"
Annan said in a statement issued here by his spokesman on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The event is a result of efforts led by the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and supported by the United
Nations to help Cambodia find a satisfactory solution to its
political crisis, Annan said.
</P>
<P>
While Ranariddh's return "is a significant step forward, much
work still remains to be done to ensure that the elections fully
do justice both to the terms of the Paris Agreement and to the
gains of Cambodia during UN Transitional Authority in Cambodia
(UNTAC) and since," Annan added. (UN-Cambodia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States on Monday expressed its
disappointment over failure of a mission by its special envoy
Dennis Ross for reviving the deadlocked peace process in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
"We have been unable to bridge the gaps on the hard questions,"
State Department spokesman James Robin told reporters. He said
the peace process "is in dire straits."
</P>
<P>
Ross has asked Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to
back Washington's proposal that Israel withdraw from 13 percent of
the West Bank in several stages within 12 weeks with each stage
accompanied by Palestinian security gestures.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli leader, however, said he did not expect a
last-minute breakthrough. He said only Israel will decide its
security needs and from that the scope of a long-delayed pullback.
(US-Mideast) 
</P>
