Mohammadi in 54 kg, Mohammad Talaie and Alireza Dabir in 58 kg,
Abbas Haj-kenari in 63 kg, Masood Jamshidi in 69 kg, Majid Khodaie
and Pejman Rastegar in 76 kg, Alireza Heidari and Fereydoun
Qanbari in 85 kg, Abbas Jadidi in 97 kg and Alireza Rezaie in 130
kg.
</P>
<P>
Iran, Japan, Germany, Russia, Cuba and the U.S. will compete in
the tournament in Oklahoma. Iran will face Japan, Germany and the
U.S. on April 5 before going against Russia and Cuba on the last
day of the competitions.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Wrestling Federation decided to send the Iranian
national wrestling team to the U.S. after an American free-style
team bagged one gold and two silver medals from an international
wrestling tournament held in Tehran last month.
</P>
<P>
Political analysts claimed that the two countries tried to
follow a "wrestling diplomacy" in order to pave the way for
normalization of their relations which were severed in 1980 after
the Iranian students occupied the U.S. embassy in Tehran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
