<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 30 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks fell on Monday with
the Dow Jones industrial average down 13.96 to close at 8,782.12.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip index extended losses since Wednesday as
investors have been worried about the impact of the Asian
financial crisis which may be reflected by lower corporate profits
in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, declining issues led advancers
with 496.70 million shares changing hands down from 579.60 million
previously, according to preliminary figures.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P's 500 stock list dipped 3.13 to 1,092.31 and the NYSE
composite index dived 0.91 to 568.89.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 4.92 to
1,818.70 and the small-company-dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index was down 1.88 to 736.45.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar hit a seven-month high against the German mark
and a two-month high against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.8474 marks
and 132 yen, up from 1.8266 marks and 130.33 yen respectively on
Friday. 
</P>
