<HEADLINE> U.S. Says no Proposal to Base Diplomat in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The United States has no
proposals "on the table" to base a U.S. diplomat in Tehran, State
Department spokesman James Rubin said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He was dismissing as groundless a report from the New York
Times, which said last week that Washington had offered to
appoint an official from the U.S. Information Agency to be
stationed at the Swiss mission in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the newspaper report at a regular briefing, Rubin
said: "It sounds to me like the reporter was talking to someone
who wasn't in the know."
</P>
<P>
"When I saw that story, I asked the people who do know. And
they indicated to me that that particular proposal was not on
the table," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss embassy in Tehran has handled all U.S. diplomatic
correspondence with Iran since the United States and Iran cut
ties in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries have gradually begun to
improve since the election last year of a new Iranian president
Mohammad Khatami. 
</P>
